<h2 id="devel">Contacting the developers</h2>
<p>Bug reports and questions about NetSurf can be raised in the
following forums.</p>

<h3>Mailing list</h3>
<p>The <a href="http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/netsurf-develop">netsurf-develop</a>
mailing list is for discussion of NetSurf. If you are interested in NetSurf's
development, please subscribe to this list.</p>

<h3>IRC channel</h3>
<p>The #netsurf-develop IRC channel on the IRCNet network is also for
discussion of NetSurf.</p>

<h3>Bug tracker</h3>
<p>Please submit any bugs to the
<a href="http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?group_id=51719&amp;atid=464312">bug
tracker</a>.</p>

<p>If you want to contribute to the NetSurf project, please contact the
developers on the Mailing List or on IRC.</p>

<h2 id="bugs">Reporting bugs</h2>
<p>We are very much open to bug reports.  Following these simple guidelines saves time for everybody:</p>

<ol>
<li>Check that the bug exhibits itself in the latest version 
<a href="http://netsurf.strcprstskrzkrk.co.uk/">available for download</a> at
the time.</li>
<li>Try to find a reproducible way of triggering the bug.</li>
<li>If a specific site is failing, give the full URL.</li>
<li>If you can narrow a bug down to a minimal test-case, then that's great.
Please provide it as it's likely to speed up a fix. (Don't worry if you
can't.)</li>
<li>Check the <a href="progress">progress</a> page and the
<a href="http://cvs.semichrome.net/netsurf/Docs/">TODO lists</a> to check
that something has actually been implemented.</li>
</ol>

